---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// Update this whenever the policy changes.
const lastUpdated = 'June 19, 2026';
const contactEmail = 'huezo.dev@gmail.com';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Shopping List"
  description="Privacy Policy for the Shopping List Android app. We don't collect your data — everything is stored locally on your device."
>
  <article class="legal container">
    <header class="legal-header">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains how the <strong>Shopping List</strong>
      mobile app (the &ldquo;App&rdquo;) handles your information. We built the App
      with privacy in mind: <strong>it does not collect, transmit, or share any
      personal data</strong>. Everything you create in the App stays on your device.
    </p>

    <h2>The short version</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We do <strong>not</strong> collect personal information.</li>
      <li>We do <strong>not</strong> require an account or sign-up.</li>
      <li>Your lists, products, and categories are stored <strong>only on your phone</strong>.</li>
      <li>We do <strong>not</strong> have servers that receive your data.</li>
      <li>We do <strong>not</strong> sell or share your data with anyone.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Information we collect</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>None.</strong> The App does not ask for your name, email, phone
      number, or any other personal information. There is no registration and no
      login.
    </p>

    <h2>Data you create in the App</h2>
    <p>
      Any content you add &mdash; such as shopping lists, products, quantities,
      and categories &mdash; is saved locally on your device using your phone&rsquo;s
      on-device storage. This information never leaves your device and is not
      accessible to us or to any third party. If you uninstall the App or clear
      its data, this information is permanently deleted.
    </p>

    <h2>How your data is stored</h2>
    <p>
      All App data is kept in a local database on your device. We do not operate
      any backend service, cloud sync, or remote database for the App, so there
      is no copy of your data anywhere other than your phone.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      The App does not integrate analytics, advertising, or tracking SDKs, and it
      does not send your information to third parties. If the App is distributed
      through the Google Play Store, Google may collect certain technical
      information (such as installs or crash data) under
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google&rsquo;s
      Privacy Policy</a>. That data is handled by Google, not by us.
    </p>

    <h2>Permissions</h2>
    <p>
      The App only uses the device permissions required for it to function. It
      does not access your contacts, location, camera, or microphone for the
      purpose of collecting personal data.
    </p>

    <h2>Children&rsquo;s privacy</h2>
    <p>
      The App does not collect any personal information from anyone, including
      children. It is safe for users of all ages.
    </p>

    <h2>Your control over your data</h2>
    <p>
      Because all data lives on your device, you are always in full control. You
      can edit or delete your lists at any time within the App, or remove all
      data by uninstalling the App or clearing its storage in your device
      settings.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will
      revise the &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date at the top of this page. Continued
      use of the App after changes are posted means you accept the updated policy.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact us</h2>
    <p>
      If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can reach us at
      <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 760px;
    padding-block: var(--space-5xl);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 17px;
  }

  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
  }

  .legal h1 {
    font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 44px);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .legal-updated {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 15px;
  }

  .legal h2 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 22px;
    margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .legal p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .legal ul {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .legal strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .legal a {
    color: var(--primary-light);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .legal a:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
</style>
